title: For Sale:  Professional Grade Colloidal Silver
postcontent:
Professional Grade Colloidal Silver Now Available.

Proper Colloidal Silver by definition, created with a medical grade unit under extremely controlled conditions. 

Deep Amber in color, which indicates a true colloidal silver solution.

Ionic silver also available (up to 18-20 ppm) which is a clear solution (often portrayed as a colloidal solution).

All solutions in a UV protective bottle, bottled and sealed immediately after production.

Solutions come in a 16 or 32 oz container. 

16 oz colloidal silver.... $35
32 oz colloidal silver.... $65

16 oz ionic silver .... $ 25 (8-10 ppm) $30 (18-20 ppm)
32 oz ionic silver .... $ 45 (8-10 ppm) $55 (18-20 ppm)

Pictures upon request.
Open to trades & other unique offers. (Looking for .40 and 7.62x 39 ammo too!) 

I've been making colloidal silver for over 5 years, and only now have begun to start to play with the idea to selling my production. Created in extremely controlled batches limited to 32oz, to be assured of a pure, true substance.

It's not up to me to tell you the extraordinary benefits of Ionic & Colloidal silver, or silver in general, but it is fair for you to know when you seek elsewhere:

It's inadvisable to drink ionic silver (clear solution) because the silver ions attach to the chloride in your stomach and becomes silver chloride, which extremely dilutes the effectiveness of the silver solution. I think this is because of silver chloride has an extraordinarily low solubility in water, and we're practically mostly water. 

So ionic (a charged form of silver) would be effective for the skin, eyes, nose, ears... pretty much anywhere where chloride is not present makes sense. 

Due your due diligence, I make no claims to the effectiveness/ineffectiveness of silver solutions, I just make the absolute best silver solutions I know how to make.

Just pour from the bottle of any colloid, to avoid contamination, don't drink right from the bottle. If your solution is compromised, it will become cloudy, and with colloids will change color(when a colloidal solution is clear, it's practically dead).

title: For Sale:  1911 IWB Leather Holster
postcontent: For the closest in concealment, this Inside-The-Waistband (IWB) leather holster gives you the deep concealment of inside the pants with a high inner body to protect your shirt or skin from the sharp edges and also to keep the finish of your pistol protected from moisture. Molded on the inside for extra retention, the top of the holster is also reinforced to allow one handed re-holstering. Inside the waistband (IWB) holsters provide the most comfortable and effective concealed carry method for most people. All parts of the holster and pistol that ride below the top of the pants (or skirt) are hidden, making it less likely that the covering garment will be pulled up and expose the holster. The shirt guard is to keep leather between the slide and your body, and to increase comfort and prevent your shirt from blocking the gun holster. The pants and belt hold the pistol close to the body for a flatter profile. This holster is made to fit belts up to 2‚Äù wide and attaches by a metal spring clip.

No cracks or repairs. Metal surfaces are free of rust or corrosion. The modified Mauser action is tight and works perfectly.

The .303 Pattern 1914 (or P-14) was a British service rifle of the First World War. A bolt action weapon with an integral 5-round magazine, it was principally contract manufactured by companies in the United States; Winchester, Remington & Eddystone. It served as a sniper rifle and as second line and reserve issue until being declared obsolete in 1947. The P-14 was the successor to the P-13 Enfield and the predecessor of the U.S. Rifle M1917 Enfield.
